bio:
This node is both, an onboarding node and a routing node for the wider network.

For channels <8M sats there is no liquidity management and zero fee.
For channels >8M sats I may manage liquidity and apply a fee schedule.
Target connectivity: 1000 nodes

Since the high fee environment started, I stopped actively participating in liquidity triangles. I still open balanced channels upon requests. Contact me via my email (admin@masterofpearls.net)


(archived section):

I release 4M,2M,1M,500k,250k swaps from time to time. If the swaps of your preferred size are taken, wait for the next slot - or open a swap yourself. I see lots of nodes opening more then one channel to my node.  This is sub-optimal.
You can always contact me if you need a custom channel. I usually reply within a day.

I also open balanced channels upon requests.

I try to do an initial rebalance when I can and the fees are negligible, but after that you got to manage your own liquidity. 

I give rating after the initial rebalance finished or I deem it impossible (because liquidity shifted).  

If you need to reach out you can contact me either through twitter or email (admin@masterofpearls.net)

The node has basic liquidity management to protect against routing failures. This means you need to submit multiple transactions to drain a channel completely. This also means the channel will be disable when it drops below a critical level of local balance. This is not a problem, as the channel can route inward, but maybe confusing for newcomers.

bio:
Watchtowers are an important component of the Lightning Network, which is a second-layer Bitcoin payment channel network. Their main purpose is to protect users from potential fraud or attacks from their channel partners.
In practice, watchtowers are services that constantly monitor users' payment channels. If a node on the network attempts to send a fraudulent transaction through a channel, the watchtower intervenes immediately, sending an emergency closure transaction to safeguard the funds of the involved users.

Watchtowers are particularly useful for users who cannot constantly monitor their payment channels, such as if they are offline for an extended period of time. In this case, the watchtower continues to monitor the channel for them and intervenes in case of any issues.

It's worth noting that the use of watchtowers is optional. Users can choose not to use them and monitor their payment channels independently. However, for anyone looking to have an extra layer of security on their Lightning Network payment channels, watchtowers are a recommended choice.

bio: The Bitcoin Lightning Network is to me, not necessarily a means for generating wealth from fees or getting rich operating channels (although, that may entirely be possible in the long run).  Rather it is more about decentralized, trustless, permission-less payments being made available to all, with low or no fees. Most importantly however is that Lightning takes the fees being charged by Visa, MC, DISC, AMEX, Paypal, Venmo, the government, etc. out of the hands of these international mega-corporations and elites and gives them back to the common man in the form of sats for low fees as a node operator or cost savings with  little to no fees at all for the common user.
name: John E. BTC

bio: HYDRANODE is a manager of channels on the Bitcoin Lightning Network (BTC-LN) using the TOR anonymization network. This network enables speedy and cheap transactions, but the reliability of which is dependent on the quality of the operating NOD. Configuring a high-quality and functional NODE requires considerable knowledge of the issues in Linux server administration, security, and mechanics of transactions with opening or closing the channels. That's not all. In addition, if you want to implement Bitcoin Lightning (BTC-LN) transactions into your business, you must also master the technicalities of recording transactions and correctly accounting following local legislation. HYDRANODE can help you with all of this.

bio:
Watchtowers are an important component of the Lightning Network, which is a second-layer Bitcoin payment channel network. Their main purpose is to protect users from potential fraud or attacks from their channel partners.
In practice, watchtowers are services that constantly monitor users' payment channels. If a node on the network attempts to send a fraudulent transaction through a channel, the watchtower intervenes immediately, sending an emergency closure transaction to safeguard the funds of the involved users.

Watchtowers are particularly useful for users who cannot constantly monitor their payment channels, such as if they are offline for an extended period of time. In this case, the watchtower continues to monitor the channel for them and intervenes in case of any issues.

It's worth noting that the use of watchtowers is optional. Users can choose not to use them and monitor their payment channels independently. However, for anyone looking to have an extra layer of security on their Lightning Network payment channels, watchtowers are a recommended choice.

bio:
ANANSI is an Akan folktale character and the Akan God of Stories, Wisdom, Knowledge, and trickery. The form of a spider is the most common depiction of Anansi.

Taking the role of trickster, he is also one of the most important characters of West African, African American and West Indian folklore.

Originating in Ghana, West Africa, these spider tales were transmitted to the Caribbean by way of the transatlantic slave trade. Anansi is best known for his ability to outsmart and triumph over more powerful opponents through his use of cunning, creativity and wit.

Despite taking on the role of the trickster, Anansi's actions and parables often carry him as protagonist due to his ability to transform his apparent weaknesses into virtues.

He is among several West African tricksters including Br'er Rabbit and Leuk Rabbit, who have persisted in popular culture globally.
name: ANANSI

bio: This node uses force lightning as its main power source. It also uses a back up power supply that is generated by 4 cockroaches strapped to a gerbil running wheel. You know that cockroaches can survive a nuclear holocaust so its highly unlikely that this node will ever fail. For connection this node uses a connection to all living beings also known as the force. For backup connection it uses a combination of smoke signals and mirror flashes that is then transferred to a digital connection via a 28.8kbp/s baud modem. These things never died right? This is one hard node to beat. Awesome force lightning for power and connection primarily with unbreakable backup power and connection! What could go wrong!

bio:
Welcome to W Group Holding's Lightning Node dedicated to providing lightning-fast, secure, and reliable enterprise finance services. 

W Group Holding is a trusted name in the world of enterprise finance. With decades of experience and a commitment to excellence, we offer a comprehensive suite of financial services tailored to the unique needs of businesses. Our Lightning Node is an extension of our commitment to cutting-edge technology and efficiency.

Services
1. Instant Payments: Our Lightning Node enables lightning-fast payments, ensuring that your business transactions are settled quickly and efficiently.

2. Liquidity Support: W Group Holding provides liquidity to the Lightning Network, ensuring smooth and uninterrupted payment flows for businesses of all sizes.

3. Secure Transactions: Security is our top priority. We implement robust security measures to protect your transactions and funds.

4. 24/7 Availability: Our Lightning Node is online 24/7, ready to facilitate your enterprise finance needs around the clock.

5. Competitive Fees: We offer competitive fees, making enterprise finance cost-effective for your business.

Contact Us:
Have questions or need support? Reach out to us at dev@siamintech.co.th

W Group Holding is dedicated to propelling your enterprise into the future of finance. Connect to our Lightning Node today for fast, secure, and efficient financial transactions.

bio:
Hello, passionate Bitcoin enthusiasts from around the world! I'm delighted to introduce myself as a fervent supporter of the Bitcoin network, and the proud operator of the this Bitcoin Node. Step into the extraordinary realm of decentralized finance with me!

At this Bitcoin Node, we are dedicated to fortifying the integrity, security, and decentralization of the Bitcoin network. Powered by an myNode installation on a Raspberry Pi 4, our setup is rock-solid. With an remarkable 1TB SSD storage, we effortlessly process and validate Bitcoin transactions, guaranteeing absolute accuracy and security for the blockchain.

Embracing the Bitcoin Network, our Bitcoin Node ensures swift and dependable access to blockchain data, facilitating seamless synchronization and efficient transaction validation. The high-performance of our configuration enhances the node's responsiveness and reliability, making it a force to be reckoned with.

Situated on the mesmerizing planet Earth, our Bitcoin Node firmly believes in the fundamental principles of financial freedom and censorship resistance, which lie at the heart of the Bitcoin revolution. By running this node, we actively engage in the Bitcoin ecosystem, independently validating transactions and blocks to promote transparency and trust.

Don't hesitate to reach out and connect with me. Let's dive deep into captivating discussions about all things Bitcoin. Whether you're curious about blockchain technology, need assistance with setting up your own node, or simply want to engage in riveting conversations about the latest developments in the crypto world, I'm here to offer my unwavering support.

We are actively supporting the following initiatives: 
*) Comics to educate people about the wonderfull world of Bitcoin and other Cryptocurrencies. https://CryptoComicStories.com/ 
*) Video page and Nostr integration, where the technology is fully based on lightning. 

Have a look and support the Bitcoin education as well!

Together, we have the power to shape the future of finance and empower individuals with the incredible concept of financial sovereignty through decentralized technology. Join me on this thrilling journey!
name: ₿⚡0308fd0d35fe851aeb67

bio:
Long time running, reliable and powerful server fully dedicated to LN.

* UPS powered
* RAID storage
* high available networking

I dynamically adjust fees to optimize flow and try to never let channels capital inactive.

Both automated and manual adjustments are applied.

When appropriate, I apply zero base fees (not always, tho).

Open to requests, questions and collaborations via DM on this platform.

The name of the node is taken from an expression that Einstein used to describe some effects of quantum mechanics, saying it would allow "spooky action at a distance". 

He was trying to convey his discomfort with the idea that particles could be instantaneously connected across vast distances, seemingly defying the laws of classical physics.

In the same way, the Lighting Network allows instant payments to nodes across vast distances.
name: SpookyPaymentAtADistance

bio:
We're in this for the long run. For an open and free society, against authoritarian control. 

Therefore we will not partake in such platforms requiring phone number like Telegram/Discord/Twitter/Facebook/Wechat/Signal, and neither should you.

Good alternatives: XMPP, Matrix, PGP e-mail, encrypted IRC.

We would like to get together a social fabric where node operators can communicate freely, privately, and securely with each other. The LN community will need to leave Telegram and Discord. Let's do it before the problem gets practical. Leave comment on this profile for your thoughts and ideas on how you would like to see this happen.

bio:
This ain’t the worst node you’ve ever seen.  Making this node aged me several years in the matter of a few days.  My family doesn’t recognize me anymore.  Exiled from the home, I live in a box (but a nice box).  My 1984 Seiko calculator watch is actually running the node.  That and its 56k modem are powered by remnant charge from discarded batteries that I scrounge.  For heat sink and protection, the whole mess is wrapped in used tinfoil and candy wrappers.

I know that sounds pretty bad, but when end times arrive, you know my node and I will be online, running lean and mean.  I’ll be there for you when much fancier rigs have fallen to raiders and/or the EMP.  My chaos-inspired rebalancing script draws from BASIC and the movements of a pack of rats in my alley.

bio:
Watchtowers are an important component of the Lightning Network. Their main purpose is to protect users from potential fraud or attacks from their channel partners. In practice, watchtowers are services that constantly monitor users' payment channels. If a node on the network attempts to send a fraudulent transaction through a channel, the watchtower intervenes immediately, sending an emergency closure transaction to safeguard the funds of the involved users.
https://frznode.com/wtforall.html

Privacy oriented tools at https://frznode.com

bio:
Numerous new channel opportunities:
A) 6Msat minimum for new incoming swaps/pool
B) NOW OFFERING CHANNELS VIA LSPS1 using BOS offer-channel-open │ lsp_server_running: 036eb65676a65660e4c1ffd728d88b3d82d027d416fad59867471fe2123de0ab27
C) PM to coordinate a dual funding using BOS - LND instead
D) Open a channel and we'll balance 1M+ to make it a good routing channel.
E) USE your pool credits here to receive a channel - PM with your request

MORE INFO:
#zerobasefee on balanced channels to other #zerobasefee nodes.
Lower routing fees with swap partners, focusing on balanced channels.
Private channels welcomed with even lower fees!
ALSO AVAILABLE: PUSH Channels, PM for details.
Join the Federation by pledging at ShireSociety.com and
Post to t.me/anarchogaming to connect AFK/IRL.
Message to negotiate a liquidity swap!

TOR DOS ATTACK - UPDATE October 28, 2022: 
ALL Systems recovered to normal operations.
Steps taken to stabilize channel connections:
1) Clearnet IP added to reduce traffic on TOR connections.
2) I2P added to Bitcoind connections to reduce traffic on TOR connections.
3) Limiting total channels to a target of 80-120, with a preference given to channels 10M+ sats, decent inbound liquidity, clearnet IP highly encouraged for all new channel partners to setup, such as using tunnelsats. (fewer low capacity channels = less potential TOR connections).
4) Closing or raising fees on all channels under 5M (fewer low capacity channels = less potential TOR connections).
5) Reconfigured lnd for easier routings through channels.

bio:
Reborn under a stronger sky, ready to play the bigger game.

⚡️ Xeon E5 1660 3.3Ghz 6-core CPU

 🐏 64GB of ECC RAM

 💽 OpenZFS mirrored pool with 6 parallel SSD's

 🔋 UPS with 1.2kWh battery

I was managing a smaller node which reached a sensible reputation on Plebnet, and thanks to some lucky incidents I leveled up and am now building KnockOnWood's capacity, evaluating each next step as I go.
The growth of the node won't be fast, but I expect it to be steady.
I plan to reach 6BTC total cap for starters, which is probably going to further increase as long as I get satisfying results.

The node is automated, I coded my own logic for fees and rebalances, and my scripts have been abundantly put to the test with my previous node, to the point where I trust them with my liquidity.
Fees usually start from 1000ppm and go from there depending on traffic, or lack thereof, so we will have to probably wait a few weeks until forwards reach best performance.

There's a medium-long term project behind KnockOnWood, which will be revealed in case the right conditions present themselves, until then we will at least try to be an excellent peer to our valued vertices.

bio:
Watchtowers are an important component of the Lightning Network, which is a second-layer Bitcoin payment channel network. Their main purpose is to protect users from potential fraud or attacks from their channel partners.
In practice, watchtowers are services that constantly monitor users' payment channels. If a node on the network attempts to send a fraudulent transaction through a channel, the watchtower intervenes immediately, sending an emergency closure transaction to safeguard the funds of the involved users.

Watchtowers are particularly useful for users who cannot constantly monitor their payment channels, such as if they are offline for an extended period of time. In this case, the watchtower continues to monitor the channel for them and intervenes in case of any issues.

It's worth noting that the use of watchtowers is optional. Users can choose not to use them and monitor their payment channels independently. However, for anyone looking to have an extra layer of security on their Lightning Network payment channels, watchtowers are a recommended choice.

bio:
Initech's Lightning Node

Welcome to the Lightning Node operated by Initech. This node is primarily established to enable seamless Bitcoin Lightning Network transactions for Initech's customers.

Purpose: Facilitating fast, secure transactions for Initech's services and products, ensuring a superior payment experience for our customers.

Connectivity: Maintained for high reliability and strong network connectivity, we aim for consistent uptime and efficient payment processing.

Collaboration: We welcome connections with other nodes to strengthen the network. Interested parties for mutual channel openings are encouraged to contact us.

Focus: As a business-centric node, we prioritize transaction reliability and maintain sufficient channel liquidity to accommodate our customers' needs.

Security: Initech upholds rigorous security standards to protect our node and transactions.
